pr_title: nmstatectl: allow route rule filtering by interface
pr_body:
Signed-off-by: SudhanAruna <sudhan.aruna.97@gmail.com>

Added Route Rule filter 
For Issue #935
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 392972483, 'comment_body': 'A rule is pointing to a route table, route table contains route next hop to interface.

`fnmatch.fnmatch(rule, pattern)` will always return False.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 3, 16, 12, 12, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cathay4t', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 393252646, 'comment_body': 'This is not needed. You can find the `next-hop-interface` in Route class. Thanks!', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 3, 16, 19, 7, 19, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ffmancera', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 393253043, 'comment_body': 'Please, use the existing constant from the schema `Rule.NEXT_HOP_INTERFACE`.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 3, 16, 19, 8, 10, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ffmancera', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 393253215, 'comment_body': 'This change is not needed.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 3, 16, 19, 8, 32, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ffmancera', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 399005765, 'comment_body': 'The rule rule does not have `Route.NEXT_HOP_INTERFACE`.

A suggestion on the approach. The `_filter_routes()` has got all interested routes, you just need to search whether
any rule is pointing to the route table of those routes.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 3, 27, 2, 48, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cathay4t', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 399111863, 'comment_body': '@cathay4t 
I have made the changes so that route rule filters rule which match the table id in filtered route.
', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 3, 27, 8, 46, 50, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'SudhanAruna', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 399280586, 'comment_body': 'The state does not contain `Route.TABLE_ID`.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 3, 27, 13, 54, 23, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cathay4t', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 399289455, 'comment_body': "Sorry, I'll work on that. Thank you for the example yml file ", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 3, 27, 14, 7, 19, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'SudhanAruna', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: libnmstate-varlink: Implementing varlink support for libnmstate
pr_body:
Implemented varlink support for libnmstate functions (show, apply, commit and rollback)
Added test cases for varlink service
Integrated with setup.py
Added README file

Signed-off-by: Arunagirinadan Sudharshan <sudhan.aruna.97@gmail.com>
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 469425374, 'comment_body': 'Please move all the information about the systemd support to the systemd implementation PR.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 12, 17, 31, 28, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ffmancera', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 469439374, 'comment_body': 'Sorry for that. I have fix it', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 12, 17, 55, 38, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'SudhanAruna', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 471317268, 'comment_body': 'There might be a race problem when multiple `get_logs()` been invoked which is actually possible as
varlink service is async.

Each `NmstateVarlinkService.Show()` should have its logger created and cleaned before return.
The same also applied to other `NmstateVarlinkService` methods.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 17, 8, 19, 2, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cathay4t', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 471319244, 'comment_body': 'This should be created by `start_varlink_server()` or other functions instead of shared at module level.

The same reason for the race problem of logger.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 17, 8, 22, 51, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cathay4t', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 471319978, 'comment_body': "Should be `gen_varlink_server()` to make sure they don't share the `varlink.Service`", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 17, 8, 24, 16, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cathay4t', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 472760079, 'comment_body': 'nit: This blank line is not needed.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 19, 6, 34, 22, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ffmancera', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 472761230, 'comment_body': 'This patch should not modify this.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 19, 6, 35, 50, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ffmancera', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_body:
Implemented the systemd service for nmstate-varlink
Added test cases for nmstate-varlink systemd services
    
Signed-off-by: Arunagirinadan Sudharshan <sudhan.aruna.97@gmail.com>
pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 473018301, 'comment_body': '`sudo` is required.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 19, 13, 13, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cathay4t', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 473018517, 'comment_body': 'sudo', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 19, 13, 13, 37, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cathay4t', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 473018658, 'comment_body': 'sudo', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 19, 13, 13, 49, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cathay4t', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 473019408, 'comment_body': 'This PR does not have resolver registered. So please remove these lines.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 19, 13, 14, 48, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cathay4t', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 473020282, 'comment_body': "We don't need to explain how varlink itself works which it might change in the future.\r\n\r\nPlease keep the document only contains the varlink interface nmstate provides.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 19, 13, 15, 54, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cathay4t', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 473021171, 'comment_body': '`Varlink service of nmstate`', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 19, 13, 17, 7, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cathay4t', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 473021417, 'comment_body': "We don't actually require `openvswitch.service`, it's optional.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 19, 13, 17, 30, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cathay4t', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 473389132, 'comment_body': 'There is a typo, this should be `Requires`.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 19, 22, 30, 2, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ffmancera', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 473587570, 'comment_body': 'Sorry fixed it.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 8, 20, 4, 53, 35, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'SudhanAruna', 'type': 'User'}]
